- Fri 3 Jan 2020
CMRE (Comite Multisectoriel de la Riposte a la maladie a virus Ebola)
[in French, machine trans., abridged, edited]
https://us3.campaign-archive.com/?u= b34a30571d429859fb249533d&id= d6d90917d0&e=b8b1e1fcf3

The epidemiological situation of the Ebola virus disease in the provinces of North Kivu and Ituri dated 2 Jan 2020:
Since the start of the epidemic, the cumulative number of cases is 3385, of which 3267 are confirmed and 118 probable. In total, there were 2232 deaths (2114 confirmed and 118 probable) and 1114 people healed;
- 389 suspected cases under investigation;
- 3 new confirmed cases in North Kivu Butembo;
- No new deaths from confirmed cases, including: No community deaths have been recorded; No death among the confirmed cases;
- No healed person has left the CTE;
- No health worker is among the new confirmed cases. The cumulative number of confirmed/probable cases among health workers is 164 (approximately 5% of all confirmed/probable cases), including 41 deaths.

News
Awareness around community watch in Mukulya in North Kivu
---------------------------------------------------------
- The Beni Sub-coordination, through its communication commission in collaboration with the commune of Bungulu organized in Mukulya in the South-West of Beni in the province of North Kivu a mass sensitization on community watch and on the rise of alerts, as part of the new campaign called "2020, new year without Ebola;"
- to this end, the assistant bourgmestre of the Bungulu commune, Mali Wa Singenda Hamza, congratulated the population in his jurisdiction for his behavior towards teams responding to the EVD and encouraged them to protect health structures;
- he also explained the risk facing the Mukulyya health area, close to the Kalunguta health zone, where Ebola positive cases have been reported in recent days;
- at the end of this awareness raising, the population of Mukulya undertook to reinforce vigilance strategies around visitors and community engagement in the fight against Ebola;
- in addition, at Biakato Mines in Ituri, an awareness day was organized on interpersonal communication on vaccination and on the dignified and secure burial protocol (EDS);
- the burning of screening devices at the Biakatoo Mines Control Point was also reported on the night of 2-3 Jan 2020 by individuals not otherwise identified.

